Named Routes in Javascript
==========================

This uncreatively named plugin installs a controller and view which creates a methods for generating named routes
in javascript.

== USAGE

This plugin injects a route automatically for your JS named routes controller.

Install, visit the following URL:

http://myapp.com/named_routes.js

Use that URL in a script tag in your app. No caching or anything, sorry.

In your javascript, you can do:

some_named_route({id: 5, name: 'joshua'})

== CREDITS

Some code and the idea came from http://gohanlon.com/2007/4/10/using-rails-named-routes-from-client-side-javascript